{"article_id":"BHpCvdwrcZEb3vdy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Super Tuesday was very good to Joe Biden .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Roughly one-third of Democrats nationwide cast their ballots for president in the first big primary election of the year ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"although not all of those ballots have yet been counted .","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Accordingly , we won ' t be unfreezing our primary forecast","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"until we have a clearer picture of the exact results .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"But we can confidently say","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"whenever it bleeps","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"and bloops back to life ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"the forecast will show Biden on the rise .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Not only did he win the states","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"he was expected to win on Tuesday ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"but he proved his cross-sectional appeal","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"by notching a few wins on what was supposed to be Sen. Bernie Sanders ' s turf .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Heading into yesterday ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"it looked like Super Tuesday was going to break down along regional lines ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"with Biden winning the Southern states","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"and Sanders winning those in the North and West .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Biden certainly held up his end of the bargain :","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Our model gave Biden a 2 in 3 chance or better","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"of winning the six Southern states of Alabama , Arkansas , North Carolina , Oklahoma , Tennessee and Virginia","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"-","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"and he carried all six by double digits .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"In fact , he exceeded our already-lofty expectations in these states .","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"For example , our average forecast in Virginia put Biden at 43 percent of the vote and Sanders at 23 percent ;","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"Biden got 53 percent in real life","depth":15},{"id":26,"text":"and Sanders 23 percent .","depth":15},{"id":27,"text":"And in Alabama , we forecasted","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"that Biden would beat Sanders 44 percent to 21 percent , on average ;","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"the final results were Biden 63 percent , Sanders 17 percent .","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"Crucially , Biden also won Texas in a close race ;","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"ABC News finally called the state at 2 a.m. Eastern","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"as Biden held a 33-percent-to-29-percent lead over Sanders .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"Texas was the most up-in-the-air state in our forecast ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"so it was always going to be a bellwether for who was having a good night on Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Of course , the fact","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"that it is worth the second-most delegates of any state","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"doesn ' t hurt either .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"But Biden ' s most impressive wins came in Massachusetts and Minnesota ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"where Sanders entered Super Tuesday as a slight favorite","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"- and Biden wasn ' t even the most likely candidate","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to upset him .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Per our forecast ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Biden had only a 1 in 5 chance","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"of carrying each state ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"and yet he won Massachusetts by 7 points and Minnesota by a daunting 9 .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Both wins showed Biden ' s ability","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"to expand his coalition outside his usual comfort zone .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Minnesota is a state","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"that has relatively few voters of color","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"( a key part of Biden ' s base )","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"and that Sanders won by 23 points in 2016 .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"But the last-minute endorsement of Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"who dropped out of the race","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"to support Biden ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"was apparently very influential .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"And in Massachusetts , Biden effectively kneecapped home-state Sen. Elizabeth Warren","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"by usurping her former base of college-educated whites ;","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"Biden carried the upper-class suburbs","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"that ring Boston .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"So far , the only states","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"that Sanders is projected or likely to win","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"are three Western states","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"- California , Colorado and Utah -","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"plus Vermont .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"Sanders was never in danger","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"of losing his home state","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"( he had a greater than 99 percent chance","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"to win Vermont ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"according to our forecast ) ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"and he may have been saved in the West by the fact","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that all three states vote primarily by mail","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"( and therefore cast many of their ballots before this week ,","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"when Biden experienced a surge of endorsements and popular support ) .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"According to exit polls ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"voters","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"who made up their mind on whom to vote for within the last few days","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"broke heavily for Biden .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"And even in states like North Carolina , Biden did merely OK among early voters","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"but cleaned up among Election Day voters .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Finally , there are a couple states","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"where we still don ' t have conclusive results .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"As of Wednesday morning , Maine was still too close to call ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"although that in and of itself is a win for Biden ;","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"we gave him only a 1 in 4 chance","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"of carrying the state entering the night .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"although some outlets","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"( though not our colleagues at ABC News )","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"have called California for Sanders ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"the results there are still very preliminary ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"since mail-in ballots can arrive as late as Friday","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"and still be counted .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"Given that California is worth 415 pledged delegates ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"the exact , final results there could make a big difference to each candidate ' s delegate math .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Indeed ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"with plenty of votes still to be counted in Colorado , Maine and Utah as well ,","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"the final national delegate totals probably won ' t be clear for several days .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":195,"left":0,"right":194,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":99,"right":193,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":105,"right":192,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":100,"right":104,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":5,"right":103,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":103,"left":6,"right":102,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent"